Name: AccountSettings
Label: Account Settings
Documentation: Represents an organization’s account settings for account teams, account owner report, and the View Hierarchy link.

Name: ActionLinkGroupTemplate
Label: Action Link Group Template
Documentation: Represents the action link group template. Action link templates let you reuse action link definitions and package and distribute action links. An action link is a button on a feed element. Clicking on an action link can take a user to another Web page, initiate a file download, or invoke an API call to an external server or Salesforce. Use action links to integrate Salesforce and third-party services into the feed. Every action link belongs to an action link group and action links within the group are mutually exclusive.

Name: ActionOverride
Label: Action Override
Documentation: Represents an action override on a standard or custom object. Use it to create, update, edit, or delete action overrides.

Name: ActivitiesSettings
Label: Activities Settings
Documentation: Represents an organization’s activity settings, and its user interface settings for the calendar.

Name: AddressSettings
Label: Address Settings
Documentation: Represents the configuration of country and state picklists.

Name: AnalyticSnapshot
Label: Analytic Snapshot
Documentation: Represents a reporting snapshot. A reporting snapshot lets you report on historical data. Authorized users can save tabular or summary report results to fields on a custom object, then map those fields to corresponding fields on a target object. They can then schedule when to run the report to load the custom object's fields with the report's data. Reporting snapshots enable you to work with report data similarly to how you work with other records in Salesforce.

Name: ApexClass
Label: Apex Class
Documentation: Represents an Apex class. An Apex class is a template or blueprint from which Apex objects are created. Classes consist of other classes, user-defined methods, variables, exception types, and static initialization code.

Name: ApexComponent
Label: Apex Component
Documentation: Represents a Visualforce component.

Name: ApexPage
Label: Apex Page
Documentation: Represents a Visualforce page.

Name: ApexTestSuite
Label: Apex Test Suite
Documentation: Represents a suite of Apex test classes to include in a test run.

Name: ApexTrigger
Label: Apex Trigger
Documentation: Represents an Apex trigger. A trigger is Apex code that executes before or after specific data manipulation language (DML) events occur, such as before object records are inserted into the database, or after records have been deleted.

Name: AppMenu
Label: App Menu
Documentation: Represents the app menu or the Salesforce mobile navigation menu.

Name: ApprovalProcess
Label: Approval Process
Documentation: Represents the metadata associated with an approval process. An approval process automates how records are approved in Salesforce. An approval process specifies each step of approval, including who to request approval from and what to do at each point of the process. Use the wildcard (*) symbol to retrieve all approval processes for all objects. You can’t use it to retrieve a subset of approval processes; syntax such as Lead.* is not supported.

Name: ArticleType
Label: Article Type
Documentation: Represents the metadata associated with an article type.

Name: AssignmentRules
Label: Assignment Rules
Documentation: Represents assignment rules that allow you to automatically route cases to the appropriate users or queues. You can access rules metadata for all applicable objects, for a specific object, or for a specific rule on a specific object.

Name: AuraDefinitionBundle
Label: Aura Definition Bundle
Documentation: Represents a Lightning definition bundle. A bundle contains a Lightning definition and all its related resources. The definition can be a component, application, event, interface, or a tokens collection.

Name: AuthProvider
Label: Auth Provider
Documentation: Represents an authentication provider (or auth provider) in your organization. An auth provider enables users to log in to your Salesforce organization using their login credentials from an external service provider such as Facebook© or Janrain©.

Name: AutoResponseRules
Label: Auto Response Rules
Documentation: Represents an auto-response rule that sets conditions for sending automatic email responses to lead or case submissions based on the attributes of the submitted record. You can access rules metadata for all applicable objects, for a specific object, or for a specific rule on a specific object.

Name: BaseSharingRule
Label: Base Sharing Rule
Documentation: This component is removed as of API version 33.0 and is available in earlier versions only. Use SharingBaseRuleinstead. Represents the base container for criteria-based and owner-based sharing rules.

Name: BrandingSet
Label: Branding Set
Documentation: Represents the definition of a set of branding properties for a community, as defined in the Branding Panel in Community Builder.

Name: BusinessHoursSettings
Label: Business Hours Settings
Documentation: Represents the metadata used to manage settings for business hours and holidays in entitlements, entitlement templates, campaigns, and cases.

Name: BusinessProcess
Label: Business Process
Documentation: The BusinessProcess metadata type enables you to display different picklist values for users based on their profile. Supports wildcard (*) only if a RecordType is specified.

Name: CallCenter
Label: Call Center
Documentation: Represents the Call Center definition used to integrate Salesforce with a third-party computer-telephony integration (CTI) system.

Name: CaseSettings
Label: Case Settings
Documentation: Represents an organization’s case settings, such as the default case owner, which case-related features are enabled, and which email templates are used for various case activities.

Name: CaseSubjectParticle
Label: Case Subject Particle
Documentation: Represents the Social Business Rules custom format for the Case Subject field on cases created from inbound social posts.

Name: Certificate
Label: Certificate
Documentation: Represents a certificate used for digital signatures which verify that requests are coming from your org. Certificates are used for either authenticated single sign-on with an external website, or when using your org as an identity provider.

Name: ChatterAnswersSettings
Label: Chatter Answers Settings
Documentation: Represents the metadata used to manage settings for Chatter Answers.

Name: ChatterExtension
Label: Chatter Extension
Documentation: Represents the metadata used to describe a Rich Publisher App that’s integrated with the Chatter publisher.

Name: CleanDataService
Label: Clean Data Service
Documentation: Represents a data service that adds and updates data in standard objects.

Name: CMSConnectSource
Label: CMS Connect Source
Documentation: Represents the connection information for external content management systems that feed content to Communities. This type extends the Metadata metadata type and inherits its fullName field.

Name: Community
Label: Community
Documentation: Represents a zone that contains Ideas or Chatter Answers objects. Zones are shared by the Ideas, Answers, and Chatter Answers features, allowing you to view and create zones from those locations.

Name: CommunityTemplateDefinition
Label: Community Template Definition
Documentation: Represents the definition of a community template.

Name: CommunityThemeDefinition
Label: Community Theme Definition
Documentation: Represents the definition of a community theme.

Name: CompactLayout
Label: Compact Layout
Documentation: Represents the metadata associated with a compact layout.

Name: CompanySettings
Label: Company Settings
Documentation: Represents global settings that affect multiple features in your organization.

Name: ConnectedApp
Label: Connected App
Documentation: Represents a connected app configuration. A connected app integrates an application with Salesforce using APIs. Connected apps use standard SAML and OAuth protocols to authenticate, provide single sign-on, and provide tokens for use with Salesforce APIs. In addition to standard OAuth capabilities, connected apps allow Salesforce admins to set various security policies and have explicit control over who can use the corresponding apps.

Name: ContentAsset
Label: Content Asset
Documentation: Represents the metadata for creating an asset file.

Name: ContractSettings
Label: Contract Settings
Documentation: Represents contract settings.

Name: CorsWhitelistOrigin
Label: Cors Whitelist Origin
Documentation: Represents an origin in the CORS whitelist.

Name: CriteriaBasedSharingRule
Label: Criteria Based Sharing Rule
Documentation: This component is removed as of API version 33.0 and is available in earlier versions only. Use SharingRules instead. Represents a criteria-based sharing rule. CriteriaBasedSharingRule enables you to share records based on specific criteria. It contains metadata for the following criteria-based sharing rules: Accounts, Campaigns, Cases, Contacts, Custom Objects, Leads, and Opportunities.

Name: CspTrustedSite
Label: Csp Trusted Site
Documentation: Represents the metadata associated with a workflow rule. A workflow rule sets workflow actions into motion when its designated conditions are met. You can configure workflow actions to execute immediately when a record meets the conditions in your workflow rule, or set time triggers that execute the workflow actions on a specific day. Use this metadata type to create, update, or delete workflow rule definitions.

Name: CustomApplication
Label: Custom Application
Documentation: CustomApplication represents a custom or standard application. In API version 29.0 and earlier, CustomApplication represents only a custom application. An application is a list of tab references, with a description and a logo.

Name: CustomApplicationComponent
Label: Custom Application Component
Documentation: Represents a custom console component (Visualforce page) assigned to a CustomApplication that is marked as a Salesforce console. Custom console components extend the capabilities of Salesforce console apps.

Name: CustomFeedFilter
Label: Custom Feed Filter
Documentation: Represents a custom feed filter that limits the feed view to feeds from the Cases object. The custom feed filter shows only feed items that satisfy the criteria specified in the CustomFeedFilter definition.

Name: CustomField
Label: Custom Field
Documentation: Represents the metadata associated with a field. Use this metadata type to create, update, or delete custom field definitions on standard, custom, and external objects or standard field definitions on standard objects.

Name: CustomLabel
Label: Custom Label
Documentation: Represents a custom label that can be localized and used in different languages, countries, and currencies. Use this type instead of CustomLabels if you want to retrieve custom labels by name.

Name: CustomLabels
Label: Custom Labels
Documentation: The CustomLabels metadata type allows you to create custom labels that can be localized for use in different languages, countries, and currencies.

Name: CustomMetadata
Label: Custom Metadata
Documentation: Represents a record of a custom metadata type.

Name: CustomObject
Label: Custom Object
Documentation: Represents a custom object that stores data unique to your organization or an external object that maps to data stored outside your org. You can also use this metadata type to work with customizations of standard objects, such as Accounts. It contains the following types: Action Overrides, Business Processes, Custom Fields, Field Sets, List Views, Named Filters (Lookup Filters), Picklists (including Dependent Picklists), Record Types, Search Layouts, Sharing Reasons, Sharing Recalculations, Validation Rules, Weblinks, and Field Types. Supports wildcard (*) for Field Sets and Record Types, but not for other components.

Name: CustomObjectTranslation
Label: Custom Object Translation
Documentation: This metadata type allows you to translate custom objects for a variety of languages.

Name: CustomPageWebLink
Label: Custom Page Web Link
Documentation: Represents a custom link defined in a home page component.

Name: CustomPermission
Label: Custom Permission
Documentation: Represents a permission that grants access to a custom feature.

Name: CustomSite
Label: Custom Site
Documentation: Represents a Salesforce site. Create public websites and applications that are directly integrated with your Salesforce organization, but don't require users to log in with a username and password.

Name: CustomTab
Label: Custom Tab
Documentation: Represents a custom tab. Custom tabs let you display custom object data or other web content in Salesforce. When you add a custom tab to an app in Salesforce Classic, it displays as a tab. When you add a custom tab to an app in Lightning Experience, it displays as an item in the app’s navigation bar. When a tab displays a custom object, the tab name is the same as the custom object name; for page, s-control, or URL tabs, the name is arbitrary.

Name: Dashboard
Label: Dashboard
Documentation: Represents a dashboard. Dashboards are visual representations of data that allow you to see key metrics and performance at a glance.

Name: DataCategoryGroup
Label: Data Category Group
Documentation: Represents a data category group.

Name: DelegateGroup
Label: Delegate Group
Documentation: Represents a group of users who have the same administrative privileges. These groups are different from public groups used for sharing.

Name: Document
Label: Document
Documentation: Represents a Document. All documents must be in a document folder, such as sampleFolder/TestDocument.

Name: DuplicateRule
Label: Duplicate Rule
Documentation: Represents a rule that specifies how duplicate records in an object are detected.

Name: EclairGeoData
Label: Eclair Geo Data
Documentation: Represents a Wave custom map chart. Custom maps are user-defined maps that are uploaded to Wave and are used just as standard maps are. Custom maps are accessed in Wave from the list of maps available with the map chart type.

Name: EmailServicesFunction
Label: Email Services Function
Documentation: Represents an email service.

Name: EmailTemplate
Label: Email Template
Documentation: Represents an email template.

Name: EmbeddedServiceBranding
Label: Embedded Service Branding
Documentation: Represents the branding for each Snap-ins deployment.

Name: EmbeddedServiceConfig
Label: Embedded Service Config
Documentation: Represents a setup node for creating a Snap-ins deployment.

Name: EmbeddedServiceLiveAgent
Label: Embedded Service Live Agent
Documentation: Represents a setup node for creating a Snap-ins Chat Live Agent deployment.

Name: EntitlementProcess
Label: Entitlement Process
Documentation: Represents the settings for an entitlement process.

Name: EntitlementSettings
Label: Entitlement Settings
Documentation: Represents an organization’s entitlement settings.

Name: EntitlementTemplate
Label: Entitlement Template
Documentation: Represents an entitlement template. Entitlement templates are predefined terms of customer support that you can quickly add to products. For example, you can create entitlement templates for Web or phone support so that users can easily add entitlements to products offered to customers.

Name: EventDelivery
Label: Event Delivery
Documentation: Represents how an event instance maps to a target payload.

Name: EventSubscription
Label: Event Subscription
Documentation: Represents a subscription to an event type.

Name: ExternalDataSource
Label: External Data Source
Documentation: Represents the metadata associated with an external data source. Create external data sources to manage connection details for integration with data and content that are stored outside your Salesforce org.

Name: ExternalServiceRegistration
Label: External Service Registration
Documentation: Represents the External Service configuration for an org.

Name: FeatureParameterBoolean
Label: Feature Parameter Boolean
Documentation: Represents a boolean feature parameter in a packaging org that has access to the Feature Management App (FMA). Feature parameters let you drive app behavior and track activation metrics in subscriber orgs that install your package.

Name: FeatureParameterDate
Label: Feature Parameter Date
Documentation: Represents a date feature parameter in a packaging org that has access to the Feature Management App (FMA). Feature parameters let you drive app behavior and track activation metrics in subscriber orgs that install your package.

Name: FeatureParameterInteger
Label: Feature Parameter Integer
Documentation: Represents an integer feature parameter in a packaging org that has access to the Feature Management App (FMA). Feature parameters let you drive app behavior and track activation metrics in subscriber orgs that install your package.

Name: FieldServiceSettings
Label: Field Service Settings
Documentation: Represents an organization’s entitlement settings.

Name: FieldSet
Label: Field Set
Documentation: Represents a field set. A field set is a grouping of fields. For example, you could have a field set that contains fields describing a user's first name, middle name, last name, and business title.

Name: FileUploadAndDownloadSecuritySettings
Label: File Upload And Download Security Settings
PluralLabel: File Upload And Download Security Settings
Documentation: Represents the security settings for uploading and downloading files.

Name: FlexiPage
Label: Flexi Page
Documentation: Represents the metadata associated with a Lightning page. A Lightning page represents a customizable screen made up of regions containing Lightning components.

Name: Flow
Label: Flow
Documentation: Represents the metadata associated with a flow. With Flow, you can create an application that navigates users through a series of screens to query and update records in the database. You can also execute logic and provide branching capability based on user input to build dynamic applications.

Name: FlowDefinition
Label: Flow Definition
Documentation: Represents the flow definition’s description and active flow version number.

Name: Folder
Label: Folder
Documentation: Represents a folder. A folder can contain documents, email templates, reports, or dashboards. You must specify the folder type (Document, EmailTemplate, Report, or Dashboard) to retrieve or deploy.

Name: FolderShare
Label: Folder Share
Documentation: Represents the settings for enhanced analytics folder sharing. Users can control access to reports or dashboards by giving others Viewer, Editor or Manager access to the folder that contains the report or dashboard.

Name: ForecastingSettings
Label: Forecasting Settings
Documentation: Represents the Collaborative Forecasts settings options.

Name: GlobalPicklistValue
Label: Global Picklist Value
Documentation: Represents the definition of a value used in a global picklist. Custom picklist fields can inherit the picklist value set from a global picklist. This type extends the Metadata metadata type and inherits its fullName field.

Name: GlobalValueSet
Label: Global Value Set
Documentation: Represents the metadata for a global picklist value set, which is the set of shared values that custom picklist fields can use. A global value set isn't a field itself. (In contrast, the custom picklist fields that are based on a global picklist are of type ValueSet.)

Name: GlobalValueSetTranslation
Label: Global Value Set Translation
Documentation: Contains details for a global value set translation. Global value sets are lists of values that can be shared by multiple custom picklist fields, optionally across objects.

Name: Group
Label: Group
Documentation: Represents a set of public groups, which can have users, roles, and other groups.

Name: HomePageComponent
Label: Home Page Component
Documentation: Represents the metadata associated with a home page component. You can customize the Home tab in Salesforce Classic to include components such as sidebar links, a company logo, a dashboard snapshot, or custom components that you create. Use to create, update, or delete home page component definitions.

Name: HomePageLayout
Label: Home Page Layout
Documentation: Represents the metadata associated with a home page layout. You can customize home page layouts and assign the layouts to users based on their user profile.

Name: IdeasSettings
Label: Ideas Settings
Documentation: Represents the metadata used to manage settings for Ideas.

Name: Index
Label: Index
Documentation: Represents an index defined within a custom big object. Use this metadata type to define the composite primary key (index) for a custom big object.

Name: InstalledPackage
Label: Installed Package
Documentation: Represents a package to be installed or uninstalled. Deploying a newer version of a currently installed package upgrades the package.

Name: KeywordList
Label: Keyword List
Documentation: Represents a list of keywords used in community moderation. This keyword list is a type of moderation criteria that defines offensive language or inappropriate content that you don’t want in your community.

Name: KnowledgeSettings
Label: Knowledge Settings
Documentation: Represents the metadata used to manage settings for Salesforce Knowledge.

Name: Layout
Label: Layout
Documentation: Represents the metadata associated with a page layout.

Name: Letterhead
Label: Letterhead
Documentation: Represents formatting options for the letterhead in an email template. A letterhead defines the logo, page color, and text settings for your HTML email templates. Use letterheads to ensure a consistent look and feel in your company’s emails.

Name: ListView
Label: List View
Documentation: ListView allows you to see a filtered list of records, such as contacts, accounts, or custom objects.

Name: LiveAgentSettings
Label: Live Agent Settings
Documentation: Represents an organization’s Live Agent settings, such as whether or not Live Agent is enabled.

Name: LiveChatAgentConfig
Label: Live Chat Agent Config
Documentation: Represents the configuration of an organization’s Live Agent deployment, such as how many chats can be assigned to an agent and whether or not chat sounds are enabled.

Name: LiveChatButton
Label: Live Chat Button
Documentation: Represents a Live Agent deployment’s settings for the button that customers click to chat with an agent and the chat window, such as the label that appears on the button and the pre-chat form that appears before a live chat begins.

Name: LiveChatDeployment
Label: Live Chat Deployment
Documentation: Represents the configuration settings for a specific Live Agent deployment, such as the branding image for the deployment and whether or not chat transcripts are automatically saved.

Name: LiveChatSensitiveDataRule
Label: Live Chat Sensitive Data Rule
Documentation: Represents a rule for masking or deleting data of a specified pattern. Written as a regular expression (regex). This object is available in API version 35.0 and later.

Name: ManagedTopics
Label: Managed Topics
Documentation: Represents navigational and featured topics managed in a community.

Name: MatchingRule
Label: Matching Rule
Documentation: Represents a matching rule that is used to identify duplicate records.

Name: Metadata
Label: Metadata
Documentation: This is the base class for all metadata types. You cannot edit this object. A component is an instance of a metadata type.

Name: MetadataWithContent
Label: Metadata With Content
Documentation: MetadataWithContent is the base type for all metadata types that contain content, such as documents or email templates.

Name: MilestoneType
Label: Milestone Type
Documentation: Represents the name and description of a milestone, which you can use in an entitlement process to track important steps in cases.

Name: MobileSettings
Label: Mobile Settings
Documentation: Represents an organization’s mobile settings.

Name: ModerationRule
Label: Moderation Rule
Documentation: Represents a rule used in your community to moderate member-generated content.Each rule specifies the member-generated content the rule applies to, the criteria to enforce the rule on, and the moderation action to take. Moderation rules help protect your community from spammers, bots, and offensive or inappropriate content.

Name: NamedCredential
Label: Named Credential
Documentation: Represents a named credential, which specifies the URL of a callout endpoint and its required authentication parameters in one definition. A named credential can be specified as an endpoint to simplify the setup of authenticated callouts.

Name: NamedFilter
Label: Named Filter
Documentation: This component has been removed as of API version 30.0 and is only provided for backward compatibility. The metadata associated with a lookup filter is now represented by the lookupFilter field in the CustomField component. Represents the metadata associated with a lookup filter. This metadata type is used to create, update, or delete lookup filter definitions. This component has been removed as of API version 30.0 and is only available in previous API versions. The metadata associated with a lookup filter is now represented by the lookupFilter field in the CustomField component.

Name: NameSettings
Label: Name Settings
Documentation: Enables or disables middle name and suffix attributes for the following person objects: Contact, Lead, Person Account, and User.

Name: Network
Label: Network
Documentation: Represents a community. Communities are branded spaces for your employees, customers, and partners to connect. You can customize and create communities to meet your business needs, then transition seamlessly between them. Use the Network component for Salesforce Communities. If you want to create zones that contain Chatter Answers and Ideas, use the Community (Zone) component.

Name: NetworkBranding
Label: Network Branding
Documentation: Represents the branding and color scheme applied to a community.

Name: OmniChannelSettings
Label: Omni Channel Settings
Documentation: Enables or disables middle name and suffix attributes for the following person objects: Contact, Lead, Person Account, and User.

Name: OpportunitySettings
Label: Opportunity Settings
Documentation: Represents organization preferences for features such as automatic opportunity updates and similar-opportunity filters.

Name: OrderSettings
Label: Order Settings
Documentation: Represents order settings.

Name: OrgPreferenceSettings
Label: Org Preference Settings
Documentation: Represents the unique org preference settings in a Salesforce org.

Name: OwnerSharingRule
Label: Owner Sharing Rule
Documentation: Represents an ownership-based sharing rule. OwnerSharingRule enables you to share records owned by a set of users with another set, using rules that specify the access level of the target user group. This component is removed as of API version 33.0 and is available in earlier versions only. It contains metadata for the following specific owner-sharing rules: Accounts, Campaigns, Cases, Contacts, Custom Objects, Leads, Account Territory and Opportunities.

Name: Package
Label: Package
Documentation: Specifies which metadata components to retrieve as part of a retrieve() call or defines a package of components.

Name: PathAssistant
Label: Path Assistant
Documentation: Represents Path records.

Name: PathAssistantSettings
Label: Path Assistant Settings
Documentation: Represents the Path preference setting.

Name: PermissionSet
Label: Permission Set
Documentation: Represents a set of permissions that's used to grant additional access to one or more users without changing their profile or reassigning profiles. You can use permission sets to grant access but not to deny access.

Name: PersonalJourneySettings
Label: Personal Journey Settings
Documentation: Represents an organization’s Adoption Manager setting, which enables or disables the Adoption Manager tool.

Name: Picklist
Label: Picklist ( Including  Dependent  Picklist)
Documentation: Deprecated. Represents a picklist (or dependent picklist) definition for a custom field in a custom object or a custom or standard field in a standard object, such as an account.

Name: PlatformCachePartition
Label: Platform Cache Partition
Documentation: Represents a partition in the Platform Cache.

Name: Portal
Label: Portal
Documentation: The Portal metadata type represents a partner portal or Customer Portal.

Name: PostTemplate
Label: Post Template
Documentation: Represents the metadata associated with an approval post template for Approvals in Chatter. With approval post templates, you can customize the information included in approval request posts that appear in Chatter feeds.

Name: ProductSettings
Label: Product Settings
Documentation: Represents organization preferences for quantity schedules, revenue schedules, and active flag interaction with prices.

Name: Profile
Label: Profile
Documentation: Represents a user profile. A profile defines a user’s permission to perform different functions within Salesforce.

Name: ProfileActionOverride
Label: Profile Action Override
Documentation: Represents an override of an ActionOverride by a user profile. You can use it to override an ActionOverride on a standard Home tab or object record page in Lightning Experience. When a user logs in with a profile, a matching ProfileActionOverride assignment takes precedence over existing overrides for the Home tab or record page specified in ActionOverride.

Name: ProfilePasswordPolicy
Label: Profile Password Policy
Documentation: Represents a profile’s password policies. Profile password policies override org-wide password policies for that profile’s users. Use ProfilePasswordPolicy to retrieve password policies for a given profile.

Name: ProfileSessionSetting
Label: Profile Session Setting
Documentation: Represents a profile’s session settings. Use ProfileSessionSetting to retrieve the session settings for a given profile.

Name: Queue
Label: Queue
Documentation: Represents a holding area for items before they are processed.

Name: QuickAction
Label: Quick Action
Documentation: Represents a specified create or update quick action for an object that then becomes available in the Chatter publisher. For example, you can create an action that, on the detail page of an account, allows a user to create a contact related to that account from the Chatter feed on that page.QuickAction can be created on objects that allow custom fields.

Name: QuoteSettings
Label: Quote Settings
Documentation: Enables or disables Quotes, which show proposed prices for products and services.

Name: RecordType
Label: Record Type
Documentation: Represents the metadata associated with a record type. Record types let you offer different business processes, picklist values, and page layouts to different users. Use this metadata type to create, update, or delete record type definitions for a custom object.

Name: RemoteSiteSetting
Label: Remote Site Setting
Documentation: Represents a remote site setting. Before any Visualforce page, Apex callout, or JavaScript code using XmlHttpRequest in an s-control or custom button can call an external site, that site must be registered in the Remote Site Settings page, or the call fails.

Name: Report
Label: Report
Documentation: Represents a custom report.

Name: ReportType
Label: Report Type
Documentation: Represents the metadata associated with a custom report type. Custom report types allow you to build a framework from which users can create and customize reports.Custom report types allow you to build a framework from which users can create and customize reports.

Name: Role
Label: Role
Documentation: Represents a role in your organization.

Name: SamlSsoConfig
Label: Saml Sso Config
Documentation: Represents a SAML Single Sign-On configuration.

Name: Scontrol
Label: Scontrol
Documentation: Deprecated. Represents an Scontrol component, corresponding to an s-control in the Salesforce user interface.

Name: SearchLayouts
Label: Search Layouts
Documentation: Represents the metadata associated with the Search Layouts for an object. You can customize which fields to display for users in search results, search filter fields, lookup dialogs, and recent record lists on tab home pages.

Name: SearchSettings
Label: Search Settings
Documentation: Represents an org's search settings.

Name: SecuritySettings
Label: Security Settings
Documentation: Represents an organization’s security settings. Security settings define trusted IP ranges for network access, password and login requirements, and session expiration and security settings.

Name: SharingBaseRule
Label: Sharing Base Rule
Documentation: Represents sharing rule settings such as access level and to whom access is granted.

Name: SharingReason
Label: Sharing Reason
Documentation: Represents an Apex sharing reason, which is used to indicate why sharing was implemented for a custom object.

Name: SharingRecalculation
Label: Sharing Recalculation
Documentation: Represents Apex classes that recalculate the Apex managed sharing for a specific custom object.

Name: SharingRules
Label: Sharing Rules
Documentation: Represents the base container for sharing rules, which can be criteria-based, ownership-based, or territory-based. SharingRules enables you to share records with a set of users, using rules that specify the access level for the target user group.

Name: SharingSet
Label: Sharing Set
Documentation: Represents a sharing set. A sharing set defines an access mapping that grants portal or community users access to objects that are associated with their accounts or contacts.

Name: SiteDotCom
Label: Site Dot Com
Documentation: Represents a site for deployment.

Name: Skill
Label: Skill
Documentation: Represents the settings for a skill used for field service or to route chats to agents in Live Agent, such as the name of the skill and which agents the skills are assigned to.

Name: SocialCustomerServiceSettings
Label: Social Customer Service Settings
Documentation: Represents the Social Business Rules custom format for the Case Subject field on cases created from inbound social posts.

Name: StandardValueSet
Label: Standard Value Set
Documentation: Represents the set of values in a standard picklist field. This type extends the Metadata metadata type and inherits its fullName field.

Name: StandardValueSetTranslation
Label: Standard Value Set Translation
Documentation: Contains details for a standard picklist translation. It returns a translated standard value set.

Name: StaticResource
Label: Static Resource
Documentation: Represents a static resource file, often a code library in a ZIP file. Static resources allow you to upload content that you can reference in a Visualforce page, including archives (such as .zip and .jar files), images, style sheets, JavaScript, and other files.

Name: SynonymDictionary
Label: Synonym Dictionary
Documentation: Represents a set of synonym groups, which are groups of words or phrases that are treated as equivalent in users’ searches. You can define synonym groups to optimize search results for acronyms, variations of product names, and other terminology unique to your organization.

Name: Territory
Label: Territory
Documentation: Represents a territory in your organization.

Name: Territory2
Label: Territory2
Documentation: Represents the metadata associated with a sales territory in Territory Management 2.0.

Name: Territory2Model
Label: Territory2 Model
Documentation: Represents the metadata associated with a territory model in Territory Management 2.0.

Name: Territory2Rule
Label: Territory2 Rule
Documentation: Represents the metadata associated with a territory assignment rule associated with an object, such as Account, in Territory Management 2.0.

Name: Territory2Settings
Label: Territory2 Settings
Documentation: Represents the metadata for the default settings for Territory Management 2.0 users to access and modify records associated with sales territories. The standard record access settings apply to accounts and opportunities. If your Salesforce org uses Private default internal access for contacts or cases, you can also set access for those records.

Name: Territory2Settings
Label: Territory Settings
Documentation: Represents the Social Business Rules custom format for the Case Subject field on cases created from inbound social posts.

Name: Territory2Type
Label: Territory2 Type
Documentation: Represents the metadata for a category of territories in Territory Management 2.0. Every Territory2 must have a Territory2Type.

Name: TopicsForObjects
Label: Topics For Objects
Documentation: Represents the ability to assign topics to objects or to remove topic assignments.

Name: TransactionSecurityPolicy
Label: Transaction Security Policy
Documentation: Represents a transaction security policy definition. Transaction Security policies give you a way to look through events in your organization and specify actions to take when certain combinations occur.

Name: Translations
Label: Translations
Documentation: This metadata type allows you to work with translations for various supported languages.

Name: ValidationRule
Label: Validation Rule
Documentation: Represents a validation rule, which is used to verify that the data a user enters in a record is valid and can be saved. A validation rule contains a formula or expression that evaluates the data in one or more fields and returns a value of true or false. Validation rules also include an error message that your client application can display to the user when the rule returns a value of true due to invalid data.

Name: WaveApplication
Label: Wave Application
Documentation: Represents the Wave Analytics application.

Name: WaveDashboard
Label: Wave Dashboard
Documentation: Represents the WaveDashboard object in the Wave Analytics application.

Name: WaveDataflow
Label: Wave Dataflow
Documentation: Represents the WaveDataflow object in the Wave Analytics application.

Name: WaveDataset
Label: Wave Dataset
Documentation: Represents the WaveDataset object in the Wave Analytics application.

Name: WaveLens
Label: Wave Lens
Documentation: Represents the WaveLens object in the Wave Analytics application.

Name: WaveTemplateBundle
Label: Wave Template Bundle
Documentation: Represents a Wave Analytics template bundle, which can be used to create Wave apps. A bundle contains a Wave template definition and all its related resources.

Name: Wavexmd
Label: Wavexmd
Documentation: Represents the WaveXmd object in the Wave Analytics application.

Name: WebLink
Label: Web Link
Documentation: Represents a custom button or link defined in a custom object.

Name: Workflow
Label: Workflow
Documentation: Represents the metadata associated with a workflow rule. A workflow rule sets workflow actions into motion when its designated conditions are met. You can configure workflow actions to execute immediately when a record meets the conditions in your workflow rule, or set time triggers that execute the workflow actions on a specific day. Use this metadata type to create, update, or delete workflow rule definitions.
